Interactive Power BI dashboard comparing product performance metrics between 2013 and 2014

ðŸ“Š Product Dashboard (2014 vs 2013)

This Power BI project presents a comparative sales analysis between Q4 2013 and Q4 2014. The dashboard highlights key performance metrics across products, customer segments, and regions to uncover business growth trends and opportunities.

ðŸ”¹ Key Insights

Sales Growth: Revenue increased from $26.42M in 2013 to $36.16M in 2014, with corresponding profit growth from $3.88M to $5.44M.

Product Performance: Top-selling products included Paseo, VTT, and Carretera, with Paseo showing significant contribution to total sales.

Regional Analysis: Canada, France, Germany, Mexico, and USA performance tracked with segment-level insights (Government, Small Business, Enterprise, Midmarket, Channel Partner).

Customer Segments: Government and Small Business segments remained dominant revenue contributors.

Discount Trends: Segment-wise and product-wise discount patterns analyzed for both years.

Seasonality: Monthly trends showed spikes in October and December for both years, with 2014 outperforming 2013 in every month.

ðŸ”¹ Features of the Dashboard

Comparative view of 2013 vs 2014 KPIs (Sales, Profit, Units Sold, Discounts).
Interactive slicers for product, country, and segment-level drilldowns.

Visual storytelling using bar charts, line graphs, and comparative visuals.

ðŸ”¹ Tools & Technology

Power BI Desktop

Data modeling with relationships across products, sales, discounts, and regions

DAX measures for KPIs and year-over-year comparisons
